<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-01T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-01T22:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2638</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Sammons</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-02T11:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Chinese naval authorities here have order Chefoo and Shanghai Naval
                            vessels proceed Chinwangtao be prepared to remove President Li if
                            necessary. Tendency here establish republic in south if monarchy
                            restored in north.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sammons</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>